Preheat your #oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9. Halve any large cauliflower florets.

Pop the @cauliflower florets{300%g} onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{1%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread them out in a single layer.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden brown and tender, ~{15-18%mins}.

Meanwhile, boil a half-full #kettle{}. Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%carton}.

Halve the @lime{1}.

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Pour the boiled water into a large #saucepan with @salt{1/4%tsp} on high heat. Add the @jasmine rice{150%g} and cook for ~{10-12%mins}.

When the cauli is halfway through cooking, remove from the oven and drizzle over the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g}.

Turn to glaze the cauli, then return to the oven for the remaining time.

When the rice has 5 mins remaining, heat a drizzle of @oil{1%tsp} in a large #saucepan on medium-high heat.

Stir-fry the @red Thai style paste{50%g} and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) until fragrant, ~{30%secs}.

Stir in the @coconut milk{200%ml}, chickpeas, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}, and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until thickened, ~{3-4%mins}.

When the rice is cooked, drain in a #sieve and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid and leave to the side until ready to serve.

Remove from the heat and add a squeeze of lime. Taste and season with @salt{}, @pepper{} or lime juice. Add a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

When everything's ready, stir the roasted cauli into the sauce.

Share your rice between your #serving bowls{}.

Spoon over the red Thai style curry.

Sprinkle over the coriander and serve with any remaining lime wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!